{
  "stem": "9963.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Later when the evacuation was, I got one letter from the underground back, and the other letter a day later, from one of my sisters what she wrote.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "When they took her to-- with the train, but first they took her to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And from the ghetto, they took her to [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Belzec, over there to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My sisters, everybody from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She had wrote a letter, and she threw that down on a place where the people were working, but she know that they will send me the letter to the camp.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I got my second letter, and exactly my sister wrote what happened.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The SS-- they took 328 people, made them take off their clothes in the middle of the street, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] men, women, and children.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My mother was between the 328 people-- took them on a truck outside the city, prepared a big hole.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The truck was tipping over and they were shooting with machine guns.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Some of them were wounded, some were killed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The rest were buried alive. 328 people-- men, women, and children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I can tell you, knowing my mother as I do, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when they made her to take off their clothes in the middle of the street, she didn't felt any pain.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "She didn't felt any pain, because she was an Orthodox woman, with a long dress, old timer.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Well-- you know-- respected in the city.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Or them, they do this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I know how she felt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And for that, I cannot forgive them, until the day I die.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[CRYING] Every time I think about it-- and I think about it very often-- it breaks my heart.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
